<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: April 8, 2026</p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how our application ("the App") handles information when using the Pinterest API to publish content automatically on behalf of the account owner.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>The App does <strong>not</strong> collect, store, or process personal data from any Pinterest user other than the account owner who has explicitly authorized the App. The only data accessed is:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Pinterest account access token (used solely to publish pins)</li>
      <li>Board identifiers required to post content</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>The access token is used exclusively to publish pins to the authorized Pinterest account via the Pinterest API. It is stored locally on the server of the account owner and is never shared with third parties.</p>

    <h2>3. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, trade, rent, or share any data with third parties. No analytics, advertising networks, or external services receive any data from this App.</p>

    <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Access tokens are stored locally and can be deleted at any time by the account owner. We do not maintain any external database or logs of Pinterest activity.</p>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>This App interacts with the Pinterest API. Pinterest's own privacy policy applies to all data processed by Pinterest. You can review it at <a href="https://policy.pinterest.com/privacy-policy" target="_blank">policy.pinterest.com/privacy-policy</a>.</p>

    <h2>6. Security</h2>
    <p>Access tokens are stored in environment variables on a private server. We take reasonable technical measures to protect this information from unauthorized access.</p>

    <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You may revoke this App's access to your Pinterest account at any time from your Pinterest account settings under "Apps and services." This will immediately invalidate any stored tokens.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy occasionally. Changes will be reflected by updating the "Last updated" date above.</p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: <a href="mailto:cubinplot@gmail.com">cubinplot@gmail.com</a></p>

    <div class="footer">
      <p>This policy applies to the Pinterest automation app owned and operated by the account holder.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
